---
// src/pages/en/about.astro
export const prerender = true;
import PostLayout from '../../layouts/PostLayout.astro';
---

<PostLayout
  title="About"
  lang="en"
  description="Vincent Xu — military finance officer turned self-taught engineer. Co-founder of DaoDao, builder of NobodyClimb. Working at the boundary of AI and product. Climbs, surfs, brews coffee."
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <link rel="alternate" hreflang="zh-TW" href="https://quidproquo.cc/about" />
    <link rel="alternate" hreflang="en" href="https://quidproquo.cc/en/about" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Serif+Display:ital@0;1&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  </Fragment>

  <div class="content about-page">
    <div class="about-grid">

      <!-- ── Left sidebar ── -->
      <aside class="about-sidebar">
        <div class="about-sidebar-inner">
          <p class="about-sidebar-name">Vincent<br />Xu</p>
          <p class="about-sidebar-title">AI Agent Engineer</p>
          <div class="about-sidebar-rule"></div>
          <nav class="about-sidebar-nav">
            <a href="https://github.com/vincentxuu" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/vincent-xu-333b7a67/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
            <a href="mailto:vincent.xu.work@gmail.com">Email</a>
          </nav>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- ── Right content ── -->
      <div class="about-body">
        <h1 class="about-h1">About</h1>

        <p class="about-intro-lede">
          My path isn't typical. I graduated from a military university with a degree in financial management, then spent nearly six years as a finance officer in the armed forces — handling payroll, auditing vouchers, managing budgets. Then I moved to Taitung to work as an educator, teaching children's philosophy and experiential education. At the same time I committed to a ten-month educator training program run by NCCU's Taiwan Experimental Education Center — a serious undertaking built around self-directed learning and field practice. Being fully immersed in that work was when I started experiencing the question firsthand: where, exactly, does learning break down?
        </p>
        <p>
          In 2020, I co-founded <a href="https://daodao.so/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">DaoDao</a> with a team of educators and engineers, trying to build a platform that makes self-directed learning visible. To make the idea real, I taught myself to code from scratch — first API, first React component, first deployment pipeline. That process gave me a more concrete feel for what it means to learn something from scratch — the gap isn't abstract to me. I crossed it myself.
        </p>
        <p>
          I transitioned into engineering professionally in 2023, working across frontend and backend, and now I'm doing AI agent development at <a href="https://maiagent.ai/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MaiAgent</a>. The attention to process and detail I built in the military, the cross-role communication instincts from education, and the habit of breaking complex problems into executable steps from self-teaching — put those three things together and you get roughly where I am today. For me, writing code isn't the point — it's a means to an end. What actually matters is building things that genuinely help people. And there's a very real satisfaction in knowing that something you made made someone's life a little better.
        </p>
        <p>
          Self-directed learning isn't just a personal habit for me — I think it's one of the most important skills a person can build. Not finishing a course and moving on, but continuously asking questions, finding resources, trying things, and adjusting from failure. That loop is the point. It's what carried me through every transition: military to education, education to engineering. DaoDao came from the same place — I want this kind of learning to be something more people can reach, not just a path a few happen to stumble onto.
        </p>
        <p class="about-pullquote">
          On learning: it's not about accumulating knowledge — it's about changing how you think. On product: it's not about stacking features — it's about deeply understanding how people actually behave. <em>Quid pro quo</em> — something for something. This blog is where I take what I've genuinely worked through and turn it into something useful for someone else. Then give a little extra.
        </p>
        <p>
          Outside work: climbing, surfing, hand-brew coffee. All three share one thing — you can't fake your way through them. The wall doesn't care how confident you are. The wave doesn't care how well you understand the theory. That kind of honest, immediate feedback is something I find fascinating — and it's quietly shaped how I think about engineering and product.
        </p>

        <h2 class="about-section-h2"><span class="about-now-label"><span class="live-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Now</span></h2>
        <ul class="about-now-list">
          <li>Doing AI agent development at <a href="https://maiagent.ai/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MaiAgent</a> — bringing AI agents into real enterprise workflows</li>
          <li>Running <a href="https://daodao.so/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">DaoDao</a> with the team — helping more people go from intention to completion</li>
          <li>Continuing to build <a href="https://nobodyclimb.cc/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NobodyClimb</a> — so every climber's story sticks around</li>
          <li>Writing this blog — putting things I've actually thought through into words</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="about-section-h2">Projects</h2>
        <div class="about-projects">
          <div class="project-card">
            <div class="project-header">
              <span class="project-name">DaoDao 島島阿學</span>
              <span class="project-badge">Co-founder</span>
            </div>
            <p class="project-desc">
              A community platform that guides self-directed learners from intention all the way to completion — so they can experience the real satisfaction of achieving their learning goals. Building an ecosystem for self-directed learning. Public practice tracking, shared challenges, and AI recommendations make progress visible and keep action going. Winner of the g0v Civic Tech Award and CommonWealth Education Innovation 100.
            </p>
            <div class="project-tags">
              <span class="ptag">Product</span>
              <span class="ptag">Behavioral Design</span>
              <span class="ptag">Node.js</span>
              <span class="ptag">Next.js</span>
              <span class="ptag">RAG</span>
            </div>
            <div class="project-links">
              <a href="https://daodao.so/" class="project-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Website →</a>
              <a href="https://app.daodao.so/" class="project-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">App →</a>
              <a href="https://github.com/daodaoedu/daodao" class="project-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub →</a>
              <a href="/posts/product/2026-03-12-daodao-product-design" class="project-link">Post →</a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="project-card">
            <div class="project-header">
              <span class="project-name">NobodyClimb</span>
              <span class="project-badge">Side Project</span>
            </div>
            <p class="project-desc">
              A climbing community platform where every climber's story sticks around. Taiwan's climbing community is growing fast, but there's no place that truly belongs to these people — NobodyClimb is meant to fill that gap, so every route, every breakthrough, and every person's journey has somewhere to be remembered.
            </p>
            <div class="project-tags">
              <span class="ptag">Community</span>
              <span class="ptag">Cloudflare Workers</span>
              <span class="ptag">LangGraph</span>
              <span class="ptag">RAG</span>
              <span class="ptag">React Native</span>
            </div>
            <div class="project-links">
              <a href="https://nobodyclimb.cc/" class="project-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Website →</a>
              <a href="https://github.com/vincentxuu/nobodyclimb" class="project-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub →</a>
              <a href="/posts/product/2026-03-12-nobodyclimb-product" class="project-link">Post →</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

